@startuml activity_corrective
!pragma useVerticalIf on
title Activity Diagram — Corrective Maintenance Workflow

|Technician|
start
:Identify equipment fault or breakdown;
:Log corrective maintenance request;

|Maintenance Management System|
:Create corrective maintenance request;
:Send notification request;

|Notification Service|
:Send maintenance request notification;

|Supervisor|
:Receive maintenance request notification;
:Assign work order to technician;
:Track work order status;

|Maintenance Management System|
:Create work order;
:Send work order notification request;

|Notification Service|
:Send work order notification;

|Technician|
:Receive work order notification;
:View assigned work order;
:Perform corrective maintenance;
:Record labour and parts used;
:Update work order;

|Maintenance Management System|
:Update maintenance history;
:Update spare parts inventory;
:Update work order status;
:Send completion notification request;

|Notification Service|
:Send completion notification;

|Supervisor|
:Receive completion notification;
:Track completed work order status;
:Review completed work;

if (Satisfactory?) then (Yes)
    :Close work order;

else (No)
    :Request rework;

    |Maintenance Management System|
    :Update work order status\nto rework requested;
    :Send rework notification request;

    |Notification Service|
    :Send rework notification;

    |Technician|
    :Receive rework notification;
    :Perform rework;
    :Record labour and parts used;
    :Update work order;

    |Maintenance Management System|
    :Update maintenance history;
    :Update spare parts inventory;
    :Update work order status;
    :Send rework completion notification request;

    |Notification Service|
    :Send rework completion notification;

    |Supervisor|
    :Receive rework completion notification;
    :Review rework;
    :Close work order;
endif

|Maintenance Management System|
:Update work order status to closed;
:Update KPI reports;

|Administrator|
:Monitor KPI reports\n(downtime, response time,\nrepair cost);

stop

@enduml